fields.title: Orange Cat
fields.description: Impressionist painting of an orange cat. From my sketchbook.

fields.title: Timothee Chalamet
fields.description: Portrait of actor Timothee Chalamet. He was supposed to star in Dune & that one Wes Anderson movie this year but sadly both releases were delayed due to the pandemic.

fields.title: Begging
fields.description: Drawn during a first year sociology lecture. I found that doodling helps me to pay attention in certain lectures.

fields.title: Mac Demarco
fields.description: Realistic portait of musician Mac Demarco. Created in anticipation of his 2018 show in Hamilton, ON at the Raspberry farm.

fields.title: Iyla
fields.description: Impressionist painting of my best friend at a cottage in summer of 2018. Made for a school project, took inspiration from Japanese artist Hokusai and Canadian artist Alex Colville. A local band titled Slacker Justice asked me for permission to use this painting as album art - I agreed, in exchange for a free hoodie.

fields.title: Charlie in Bed
fields.description: Drawing of my pet beagle Charlie about to have a nap. One of my favourites, because of the style it is drawn in.

fields.title: Harry Potter
fields.description: Realistic portrait of Daniel Radcliffe portraying Harry Potter from Harry Potter & the Philosophers Stone.

fields.title: Pastel Drawing
fields.description: Experimentation with oil pastels, a portrait of a girl with blue hair. Done without reference.

fields.title: Billie Eilish
fields.description: Realistic portrait of Billie Eilish. I chose a photo reference where she had green hair because green is my favourite colour.

fields.title: Hamlet Kills Polonius
fields.description: I painted this for an english presentation in highschool. I referenced the Kenneth Branagh Hamlet movie.

fields.title: A$AP Rocky
fields.description: Portrait of A$AP rocky, painted because I am a fan and wanted a poster for my wall.

fields.title: Blue Carley
fields.description: Portrait of my friend Carley, but done in monochrome blue tones. Reminds me of when Violet turned into a blueberry in Charlie and the Chocolate Factory.

fields.title: Dog Portrait
fields.description: A realistic painting of a dog. He is coloured like a rottweiler, but his face shape suggests a different breed, like maybe a dachsund. I am proud of this painting.

fields.title: Abstract Eye
fields.description: An interesting abstract painting of an eye done for a school project. Not much else to say.

fields.title: Frank with Ocean
fields.description: A portrait of Frank Ocean in front of the ocean. I definitely used a reference for this one. I remember that while I was painting it, I accidentally spilled water all over it and it got ruined. I had to spend about an hour waiting for the water to dry and then fixing it. After that, I realized gouache paint was not a good choice of medium for me and I would benefit from using something more acrylic.

fields.title: MC Ride
fields.description: A friend had asked me to paint MC Ride from death grips, having nothing better to do I obliged. I do not listen to Death Grips nor do I enjoy it but i have heard that it goes it goes it goes it goes guillotineeeeeeee

fields.title: Muppets Take New York
fields.description: A painting of my friend in the big city with her two dogs. One is running away. I do not believe I explicitly used a reference for this.

fields.title: The Perfect LUV Portrait
fields.description: First off, the title is not serious - this portrait has many imperfections. Being a big Lil Uzi Vert fan in 2018, the only logical thing for me to do was to paint a realistic portrait of him, I guess. This was done from reference.

fields.title: Mathilda
fields.description: Inspired by the 1994 film LÃ©on: The Professional starring young Natalie Portman, I painted a scene from said movie. This was one of the first times I believed I might be good at painting, and I still like it.

fields.title: Silent Bob
fields.description: I'm not sure why I painted this, probably right after binge watching all the Jay and Silent Bob movies.

fields.title: First Self-Portrait
fields.description: My first self-portrait & one of my earliest paintings. My grandma said it did not look like me. It's interesting to notice that I seemed to already have an art style.

fields.title: Slice
fields.description: In my more recent work, I abandoned using references and the goal of realism. Here is an example of me trying to achieve a more creative/original style.

fields.title: Green Man
fields.description: Monochrome green face. Was displayed in Artists of Woolwich Gallery during summer of 2019.

fields.title: Blue Twins
fields.description: Two blue girls. Probably just done for practice.

fields.title: Transplant
fields.description: Another example of a painting where I was more focused on originality and not using references than the technique. Because of this, I think the concept is interesting but the execution is sort of bad.

fields.title: Purple Planet
fields.description: This was displayed in Artists of Woolwich gallery during the summer of 2019. I believe I was trying to comment on how planets and environments can be considered living things.
